<br>
City of Mist Raid on 9th March was a good success.<br>
We had 2 Jade Reavers drop.<br>
<br>
Now the hard part.  Apolgies.<br>
<br>
Firstly, I'd like to point out that this was my first time running a raid like this - and as much as I'd thought I prepared with the information I put on our website - www.wolvesofantonica.co.uk - -<br>
I didn't say enough.<br>
<br>
before I am shot down in flames I'd like to explain the looting of the Reavers, and the rolling.<br>
<br>
This is a little confusing, but this is how it happened.<br>
In future, I will not let this happen again!<br>
<br>
firstly, the raid started to break up, and people left before rolling on the reavers - a druid called Negerdar, I know for one.<br>
<br>
On the website, I talked about if more than one dropped, I'd like to take one if no one objected.  Up until the mess with the rolling, that was my intention.<br>
So, the roll was for the one remaining reaver - and believe it or not,  abraxxas rolled in the high 800's to win?.  Someone started complaining about people rolling for alts - then someone else rolled I think and scored a cool 1000 out of 1000!  Now, no one mentioned anything about rolling for alts to me, so I said that, and neglected to include that random.  To complicate things more, I then rolled for Negerdar after confirming I would.  Negerdat scored over 900 and wins.<br>
Then I get a few flaming tells saying they've never been on a raid where they couldn't roll for Alts, etc.  So, I had to think quickly.  I decided that this was exploitable on the spot, as every man and his dog would suddenly have a druid or ranger alt - honestly!  So, I decided the fairest thing I could do was stick to my oroginal decision, and let Negerdar have the Jade Reaver.<br>
<br>
It was obvious that people were not happy - and I am sure some left the raid at this point.  But I decided to give up my Jade Reaver for everyone and their Alt to roll on.  There was not a huge number of rolls, and I got 933 for myself, and rolled something pitiful for poor buvin.<br>
People thought this was for me - but I had to correct them, and I'm sure my credibility was going down faster than the Titanic.<br>
<br>
Then Brackin (Is that the warrior's name?) admitted that he doesn't have an Alt, and that he did not know what he was rolling for.  Great! What a mess!<br>
So, Come the end of the second roll, on MY reaver - the results ended up as they were at the beginning!<br>
Odds on that happening again in my lifetime?  Who knows.<br>
<br>
But let me assure you, this mess won't happen again.<br>
<br>
I am sorry if I upset anyone with my actions, but I did warn you all from the start that this was my first!<br>
<br>
I learned an aweful lot this night, and I want a special thankyou to go to Sylenn who came along against all odds to ensure we had a rogue present.  <br>
Thanks Also to Antoin for all his help in the thick of the action.<br>
Thanks to everyone for making this the success it was.  <br>
<br>
I'm so, so, sorry it didn't start as I posted, and even worse, had to fight with the raid feature to get everyone in.<br>
<br>
Sorry for any problems. stress, and anxiety I might be responsible for.  I'm hoping that in the next week or so, I will reflect on this, learn from it - and perhaps you guys might find it in your hearts to raid with me once more.<br>
<br>
At least I'll never be rolling on the reaver again!<br>
<br>
1000 humble apologies.<br>
<br>
Guildor<br>
Wolves of Antonica. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dorvum>Dorvum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(3/9/03 9:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=449.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: COM raid success and apologies.</span><hr size=1> You don't roll for alts for epic pieces. Unless the alt is there taking part in the battle. I've never been on an open raid that any Jade Reavers were reserved. Private raid sure but an open raid the reaver drops are too sporadic to reserve them. Sounds like you had alot of blue server trash raiding with you trying to put one over on you.<br>
